    "For a co-located finite volume mesh, these points correspond to the cell centers, so M is equivalent to the number of cells composing the mesh.",
    "Since the example data used in section (3) are generated by finite volume codes, we stick to this interpretation of M for the remainder of this manuscript.",
    "However, in principle, S 3 does not rely on the mesh topology or the underlying numerical method.",
    "The first step is the calculation of a metric field M ∈ R M based on the time series of N snapshots at discrete times tn of one or more scalar fields fn ∈ R M with n ∈ {1, 2,..., N }.",
    "The metric is a user-defined scalar field that should express the importance of each location pi."
